{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"All direct and transitive dependencies are extracted from the manifest and included in the vulnerability check.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: yes — pure mocks can miss resolver/parser wiring bugs across manifest + lockfile handling. REAL-INFRA: no real network required. MOCK-HIDE: yes if dependency graph resolution is mocked. LLM-DEP: no. MULTI-STEP: no.","test_description":"Run scanner against fixture projects on disk (e.g., npm with package.json+lockfile, pip with requirements+lock data) and assert the produced dependency set sent to the vulnerability-check stage includes both direct and transitive entries with expected versions.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The vulnerability database query returns results that match the exact version ranges in the manifest, not just the package name.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"MOCK-MISS: yes — mocked API responses can hide request-shape/range-encoding defects. REAL-INFRA: yes — real HTTP/API contract behavior matters. MOCK-HIDE: yes, especially for boundary versions and range semantics. LLM-DEP: no. MULTI-STEP: no.","test_description":"Against a real or production-equivalent vulnerability API endpoint over HTTP, submit dependencies with tricky semver ranges (e.g., <1.2.3, ^2.4.0, ~=1.4) and assert returned CVEs correspond to vulnerable versions within those exact ranges, not all versions of the package.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.25,"System":0.7,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The severity sorting places Critical above High above Medium above Low, with CVEs of the same severity sorted by CVSS score.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"MOCK-MISS: low — this is deterministic comparator logic. REAL-INFRA: no. MOCK-HIDE: no meaningful external dependency to hide. LLM-DEP: no. MULTI-STEP: no.","test_description":"Call the sort function with unsorted CVE fixtures spanning all severities and tied severities with different CVSS values; assert exact output order (severity rank first, CVSS descending second).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.9,"Integration":0.08,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"The manifest modification changes only the affected dependency's version, leaving all other entries unchanged.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: yes — in-memory object tests can miss real parse/serialize side effects and key reordering. REAL-INFRA: local filesystem only. MOCK-HIDE: yes if file I/O or serializer is mocked. LLM-DEP: no. MULTI-STEP: no.","test_description":"Use a real manifest file fixture with multiple dependencies and formatting nuances; execute update flow for one target package; assert only that dependency version changed and all other entries/sections are byte-stable or semantically unchanged per tool guarantees.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.75,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The auto-generated pull request is created on the real repository with the correct single-dependency diff.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"MOCK-MISS: yes — mocked git/provider clients can miss auth, branch, API, and diff packaging failures. REAL-INFRA: yes — real VCS hosting API and git behavior. MOCK-HIDE: yes, mocks often always accept PR payloads. LLM-DEP: no. MULTI-STEP: no agentic pipeline.","test_description":"In a real test repository, run scanner end-to-end to PR creation; verify PR exists remotely, changed files/diff contain only the intended dependency bump, and metadata (title/body/branch) matches policy.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.95,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"A major version bump is correctly identified as a breaking change based on semver comparison.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"MOCK-MISS: low — pure semver decision logic. REAL-INFRA: no. MOCK-HIDE: no external dependency needed. LLM-DEP: no. MULTI-STEP: no.","test_description":"Test semver comparison helper with representative pairs (1.2.3->2.0.0 breaking, 1.2.3->1.3.0 non-breaking, pre-release edge cases) and assert breaking-change classification.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.92,"Integration":0.07,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"When a breaking change is detected, PR creation is skipped and a review flag is surfaced in the scanner output.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"MOCK-MISS: yes — must validate orchestration between semver check, PR gate, and output formatter. REAL-INFRA: no external API required if PR client is a local test double with call assertions. MOCK-HIDE: partial; unit-only tests can miss pipeline wiring. LLM-DEP: no. MULTI-STEP: no.","test_description":"Execute scanner pipeline with input that triggers major bump; assert workflow status includes review-required flag/message and PR creation path is not invoked (no branch/PR artifact emitted).","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.3,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}}]}
